HEADWORD: Plagiarist
<hw>Pla"gia*rist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who
plagiarizes, or purloins the words, writings, or ideas of another, and
passes them off as his own; a literary thief; a plagiary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plagiarize</ent>⟦br⟧
